<tr>
<td><b>Gordion</b></td>
<td>Ankara</td>
<td>2023</td>
<td>The ancient city of Gordion, the capital of the Phrygian Kingdom, and the large tumuli in its surroundings, such as the Tomb of Midas.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Travel Tips</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Vast Geography:</b> The heritage sites are spread across very different regions of Turkey (from Kars in the East to İzmir in the West, from Şanlıurfa in the Southeast to Nevşehir in Central Anatolia). Consider the geographical distances when <a href="https://roadtostudy.com//turkiyede-ic-turizm-seyahat-rotalari/">planning a route</a>.</li>
<li><b>Museum Pass (Müze Kart):</b> You might consider getting a <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-ogrenci-indirimleri-firsat-kartlari/"><b>Müze Kart</b></a>, which offers entry to many archaeological sites and museums in Turkey (with the exception of some private museums) with a single card. This will be economical, especially if you plan to visit multiple UNESCO sites.</li>
<li><b>Göbekli Tepe and Çatalhöyük:</b> These two Neolithic heritage sites offer unique insights into the earliest settlement and temple structures in human history and are a must-see for archaeology enthusiasts.</li>
<li><b>Regional Combinations:</b> Some sites are close to each other, for example, Xanthos-Letoon (Antalya-Muğla) or Ephesus and Pergamon (İzmir-Aydın). You can combine these sites into a single travel itinerary.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h2 id="yurt-disinda-egitim-alan-ogrenciler-icin-turkiyenin-unesco-miraslari" class="wp-block-heading">Turkey&#8217;s UNESCO Heritage for Study Abroad Students</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students studying abroad can contribute to both their academic and personal development by visiting the UNESCO World Heritage Sites in Turkey. These sites offer students the opportunity to gain in-depth knowledge about history and culture. For example, a student can learn about ancient Roman architecture by visiting the Ancient City of Ephesus, or understand how natural formations occurred by seeing the fairy chimneys in Göreme.</p>
<h2 id="unesco-dunya-mirasi-alanlari-ile-kulturel-deneyimlerinizi-zenginlestirin" class="wp-block-heading">Enrich Your Cultural Experiences with UNESCO World Heritage Sites</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <a href="http://Türkiye&#039;nin UNESCO Dünya Mirası Alanları Rehberi" data-wplink-url-error="true">UNESCO World Heritage</a> Sites in Turkey not only offer historical and natural beauty but also enrich your cultural experiences. By visiting these sites, you can interact with local people, experience Turkish cuisine, and participate in traditional festivals. For example, while exploring the natural beauty around the hot springs in Pamukkale, you can find the opportunity to taste local dishes.</p>
<h2 id="unesco-dunya-mirasi-alanlari-ve-turkiyenin-egitim-potansiyeli" class="wp-block-heading">UNESCO World Heritage Sites and Turkey&#8217;s Educational Potential</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers students a unique experience by combining the quality education it provides in higher education with the richness of its UNESCO World Heritage Sites. During their studies, students have the opportunity to grow both academically and personally by visiting these historical and cultural sites. Furthermore, Turkey&#8217;s education system is structured in line with international standards and offers students a wide range of programs.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country that offers international students opportunities for education, cultural experiences, and an affordable lifestyle. The richness of its UNESCO World Heritage Sites provides significant contributions to students&#8217; academic and personal development. For young people wishing to study, Turkey promises a rich experience both academically and socially. If you are considering studying in Turkey, we recommend you don&#8217;t miss out on these opportunities.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-04-18T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:51:11Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-turkeys-unesco-world-heritage-sites';
