<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Le premier centre commercial de Turquie est le « Galleria », ouvert en 1988. Situé dans le quartier de Bakırköy à Istanbul, cet AVM a été un pionnier dans le domaine du shopping et du divertissement. En tant que premier exemple de centre commercial en Turquie, le Galleria s&#8217;est distingué par son architecture et les services qu&#8217;il proposait.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avec l&#8217;ouverture du Galleria, la culture des AVM en Turquie a commencé à se développer rapidement, et de nombreux nouveaux centres commerciaux ont été construits. Au fil du temps, ces centres ont commencé à offrir des services de plus en plus vastes et diversifiés.</p>
<h2 id="yurt-disindan-gelen-ogrenciler-icin-turkiyede-avm-ziyareti-ipuclari" class="wp-block-heading">Conseils pour les étudiants internationaux visitant les AVM en Turquie</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Pour les étudiants internationaux, les AVM en Turquie offrent des opportunités de shopping mais aussi d&#8217;interaction sociale. Voici quelques conseils pour rendre cette expérience plus agréable :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Profitez des réductions pour étudiants :</strong> De nombreux AVM proposent des réductions spéciales pour les étudiants. Vous pouvez en bénéficier en présentant votre carte d&#8217;étudiant pour profiter de ces <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkcede-alisveris-pazarlik-kaliplari/">réductions</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Suivez les événements :</strong> Les AVM organisent fréquemment des concerts, des expositions et d&#8217;autres événements. En y participant, vous pourrez vous amuser et rencontrer de nouvelles personnes.</li>
<li><strong>Goûtez aux saveurs locales :</strong> Dans les restaurants des AVM, vous pouvez découvrir les diverses saveurs de la cuisine turque. Déguster des plats locaux comme le kebab, le döner ou le pide enrichira votre expérience culturelle en Turquie.</li>
<li><strong>Planifiez vos achats :</strong> Bien qu&#8217;il soit agréable de passer du temps dans les AVM, il est utile de définir un budget pour <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-yerel-pazarlar/">faire du shopping</a>. Cela vous aidera à éviter les dépenses superflues.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyedeki-en-populer-alisveris-merkezleri-ve-nedenleri" class="wp-block-heading">Les centres commerciaux les plus populaires de Turquie et pourquoi</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Parmi les centres commerciaux les plus populaires de Turquie, on trouve :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Cevahir Alışveriş Merkezi (Istanbul) :</strong> Considéré comme l&#8217;un des plus grands centres commerciaux d&#8217;Europe, le Cevahir se distingue par sa vaste sélection de boutiques et ses espaces de divertissement.</li>
<li><strong>Mall of Istanbul :</strong> Se démarquant par son architecture moderne et la diversité de ses marques, le Mall of Istanbul est un lieu idéal pour le shopping et le divertissement.</li>
<li><strong>Forum Istanbul :</strong> Avec son aquarium, son parc d&#8217;attractions et ses nombreuses boutiques, il offre aux visiteurs une expérience inoubliable.</li>
<li><strong>Ankara Panora :</strong> Étant le plus grand centre commercial de la capitale, Ankara, Panora est un lieu prisé pour le shopping et les événements sociaux.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ces centres commerciaux attirent l&#8217;attention des visiteurs locaux et étrangers grâce à leur large gamme de produits, leurs options de divertissement et leurs espaces sociaux.</p>
<h2 id="avmlerde-kulturel-deneyimler-yeme-icme-ve-eglence-alternatifleri" class="wp-block-heading">Expériences culturelles dans les AVM : Options de restauration et de divertissement</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les AVM ne sont pas seulement des lieux de shopping, mais aussi des espaces offrant des expériences culturelles. En Turquie, les options de restauration et de divertissement dans les AVM sont très variées :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Aires de restauration :</strong> Les AVM abritent des restaurants proposant des saveurs de nombreuses cultures culinaires différentes. Outre la cuisine turque, il est possible de trouver des options de cuisines du monde entier.</li>
<li><strong>Cinémas et espaces de loisirs :</strong> Les AVM disposent d&#8217;options de divertissement telles que des salles de cinéma, des pistes de bowling et des salles de jeux. Ces espaces vous permettent de passer d&#8217;agréables moments avec vos amis ou votre famille.</li>
<li><strong>Espaces événementiels :</strong> Certains AVM organisent des événements tels que des expositions d&#8217;art, des concerts et des festivals. Ces activités offrent aux visiteurs une expérience culturelle.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyenin-en-buyuk-avmsi-neresi" class="wp-block-heading">Quel est le plus grand AVM de Turquie ?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Le plus grand centre commercial de Turquie est le « Mall of Istanbul », situé à Istanbul. Ouvert en 2014, ce centre commercial géant est équipé de plus de 350 boutiques, de salles de cinéma, d&#8217;espaces de divertissement et de restaurants. Le Mall of Istanbul n&#8217;est pas seulement un lieu de shopping, mais aussi un véritable espace de vie sociale.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Foire aux questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quelles marques trouve-t-on dans les AVM en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les AVM en Turquie abritent de nombreuses marques de renommée mondiale. Une large gamme de produits est proposée, allant de l&#8217;habillement à l&#8217;électronique, en passant par les articles ménagers et les cosmétiques.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quelles sont les options de restauration dans les AVM ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Dans les AVM, vous trouverez de nombreuses options culinaires différentes, comme la cuisine turque locale, ainsi que des cuisines italienne, mexicaine, asiatique et de la restauration rapide.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quel est l&#8217;AVM le plus populaire en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Le Cevahir Alışveriş Merkezi est l&#8217;un des centres commerciaux les plus populaires de Turquie, et il se distingue par sa vaste sélection de boutiques.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quelles activités pour enfants sont disponibles dans les AVM ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les AVM proposent de nombreuses activités pour les enfants, comme des aires de jeux, des salles de cinéma et des parcs d&#8217;attractions. Ces espaces permettent aux familles de passer un agréable moment avec leurs enfants.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">À quoi dois-je faire attention lorsque je fais du shopping dans un AVM ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Lorsque vous faites du shopping, il est important de définir un budget, de surveiller les réductions et de planifier vos besoins à l&#8217;avance. Vous pouvez également vivre une expérience sociale en suivant les événements organisés dans les AVM.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-04T10:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-06T09:20:39Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'la-culture-des-centres-commerciaux-en-turquie-et-limportance-du-shopping-moderne' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"A Guide to Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Enjoy the thrill of vintage and second-hand shopping! Discover the best spots in Turkey and express your unique style with one-of-a-kind pieces.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"A Guide to Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Enjoy the thrill of vintage and second-hand shopping! Discover the best spots in Turkey and express your unique style with one-of-a-kind pieces.","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"A Guide to Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Enjoy the thrill of vintage and second-hand shopping! Discover the best spots in Turkey and express your unique style with one-of-a-kind pieces.","canonicalPath":"/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-vintage-ikinci-el-alisveris/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/panduan-belanja-vintage-dan-barang-bekas-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/guide-du-shopping-vintage-et-de-seconde-main-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-15T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-15T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-15T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-15T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Student Life and Travel","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Enjoy the thrill of vintage and second-hand shopping! Discover the best spots in Turkey and express your unique style with one-of-a-kind pieces.","name":"A Guide to Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p>In Turkey, the culture of second-hand and vintage shopping is vibrant, especially in the historic and bohemian neighborhoods of its major cities. With a growing awareness of sustainability, these types of shops have become popular hubs not only for clothing but also for finding nostalgic home goods and antique pieces.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Istanbul: The Heart of Vintage and Antiques</h3>
<p>Istanbul offers the richest variety of options for those seeking both luxury vintage items and affordable second-hand finds (thrifting).</p>
<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Neighborhood / Area</td>
<td>Focus Points</td>
<td>Shop Suggestions (Examples)</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Çukurcuma &amp; Galata</strong> (Beyoğlu)</td>
<td><strong>Luxury Vintage and Antiques.</strong> Period clothing from the 1950s-80s, quality jewelry, antique furniture, and designer objects.</td>
<td><strong>Pied De Poule</strong>, <strong>Evvel Zaman İçinde</strong>, <strong>Bin Bavul Vintage</strong>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cihangir</strong> (Beyoğlu)</td>
<td><strong>Boutique Vintage and Nostalgia.</strong> More boutique and curated vintage clothing, accessories, and period lingerie.</td>
<td><strong>Mozk Vintage Shop</strong>, <strong>Closet Circuit</strong>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Kadıköy / Moda</strong> (Asian Side)</td>
<td><strong>Affordable Second-Hand (Thrifting) and Street Style.</strong> Shops that are very popular with students and young people, where prices are more accessible.</td>
<td>Independent second-hand shops and flea markets around Moda and Kadife Sokak.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Feriköy Antique Market</strong> (Şişli)</td>
<td><strong>Market Experience and Antiques.</strong> Held every Sunday. It brings together hundreds of vendors selling everything from furniture and records to porcelain and vintage accessories.</td>
<td>The parking lot area in Feriköy on Sundays.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Ankara: Historic and Academic Hubs</h3>
<p>Ankara stands out with its shops that focus on more boutique and specific styles.</p>
<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Neighborhood / Area</td>
<td>Focus Points</td>
<td>Description</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Kızılay / Around Karanfil Sokak</strong></td>
<td><strong>Youth-Focused and Affordable Second-Hand.</strong> This area, popular with students and young people, has arcades and shops where you can easily find second-hand and period clothing.</td>
<td>You can find more affordable versions of brand-name items or gently used clothing.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Çankaya / Tunalı Hilmi Caddesi</strong></td>
<td><strong>Curated Vintage and Boutiques.</strong> Home to more selective, boutique-style vintage shops that often focus on a specific era, with mid-to-high-range prices.</td>
<td>Collectible pieces, accessories from old periods, and designer clothes.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Izmir: The Cozy Vintage Vibe of the Aegean</h3>
<p>In Izmir, the second-hand culture has a more local and bohemian feel.</p>
<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Neighborhood / Area</td>
<td>Focus Points</td>
<td>Description</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Alsancak / Side streets off Kıbrıs Şehitleri Caddesi</strong></td>
<td><strong>Vintage and Boutique Shops.</strong> In the side streets that preserve the historic texture, you can find shops selling both products from Izmir-based designers and curated vintage clothing.</td>
<td>The focus is primarily on nostalgic clothing and accessories.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Kemeraltı Bazaar (Parts of it)</strong></td>
<td><strong>&#8220;Spotçu&#8221; (Discount Shops) and Antiques.</strong> Deep within Kemeraltı and its hidden hans (inns), you can discover &#8220;spotçu&#8221; shops selling old radios, clocks, porcelain, and lightly used home goods.</td>
<td>Hunting for hidden antiques in a traditional bazaar atmosphere.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Second-Hand Shopping Tips</h3>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Explore Flea Markets:</strong> Flea markets in major cities (like the Kadıköy Antique Market or Feriköy Market in Istanbul) are the best places to find the most interesting and affordable items.</li>
<li><strong>Bargain:</strong> Bargaining is part of the culture, especially at antique shops and flea markets. Don&#8217;t hesitate to make an offer.</li>
<li><strong>Check the Condition:</strong> When buying second-hand clothes, don&#8217;t forget to check zippers, seams, and for any stains. Most vintage boutiques clean their items before selling, but at markets, this is your responsibility.</li>
<li><strong>Focus on One Area at a Time:</strong> In neighborhoods like Çukurcuma, shops are located close to each other, so you can shop more efficiently by concentrating on one area.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="turkiyede-vintage-ve-ikinci-el-esya-bulmanin-yollari" class="wp-block-heading">Ways to Find Vintage and Second-Hand Items in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many ways to find vintage and second-hand items in Turkey:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Physical Stores</strong>: Vintage stores, second-hand shops, and antique dealers in cities are the most common way to access the items you&#8217;re looking for. Major cities like Istanbul, Ankara, and Izmir have numerous options.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Markets</strong>: Local flea markets and antique markets are fantastic places to find vintage items. You can often find rare and interesting pieces at these kinds of markets.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Online Platforms</strong>: Platforms like <a href="https://dolap.com/giris" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dolap</a>, Letgo, and Facebook Marketplace are very popular for buying and selling second-hand goods. You can easily find the products you&#8217;re looking for on these platforms.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Social Media</strong>: Social media platforms like Instagram and Pinterest are full of small businesses and individuals selling vintage and second-hand items. You can shop or get inspiration through these platforms.</p>
<h2 id="vintage-ve-ikinci-el-alisveriste-dikkat-edilmesi-gerekenler" class="wp-block-heading">What to Watch Out for in Vintage and Second-Hand Shopping</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some important points to consider when doing vintage and <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ikinci-el-mobilya-bulma-rehberi/">second-hand shopping</a>:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>The Item&#8217;s Condition</strong>: Get information about the general condition of the item you are considering buying. Avoiding worn-out or damaged products will help you make a long-lasting purchase.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Price Research</strong>: Try to understand the true value of the item you are buying by researching the prices of similar products. This will help you avoid overpriced items.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Seller Reliability</strong>: When shopping on online platforms, check the seller&#8217;s reliability. By reading reviews from other buyers, you can learn about their experiences in previous sales.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Return and Exchange Policies</strong>: Always check the return and exchange policies of the place you are shopping from. Returns are sometimes not accepted for vintage items, so it&#8217;s important to be informed about this.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Cleaning and Maintenance</strong>: Since most vintage items have been used in the past, they may require cleaning and maintenance. Therefore, consider the maintenance needs before buying the products.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-en-iyi-vintage-ve-ikinci-el-magazalari-nereler" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Where are the best places to find vintage items in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The best places to find vintage items in Turkey include antique shops, local markets, and online platforms. Major cities like Istanbul, Ankara, and Izmir offer a wide range of options.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What should I pay attention to when vintage shopping?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When vintage shopping, you should pay attention to factors such as the item&#8217;s condition, price, seller reliability, and return policies.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What should I pay attention to when shopping on online platforms?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When shopping online, it is important to examine product images, read descriptions, communicate with the seller, and use secure payment methods.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much do vintage items cost?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The prices of vintage items vary depending on the type, condition, and rarity of the product. It is beneficial to do price research at different stores and on different platforms.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How common is vintage shopping in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Vintage and second-hand shopping in Turkey has gained increasing popularity in recent years. The pursuit of sustainability and unique pieces makes this form of shopping attractive.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-04-15T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:51:03Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-vintage-and-second-hand-shopping-in-turkey';
