re-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"fr-FR","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/les-fetes-de-laid-en-turquie-activites-et-recommandations/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/les-fetes-de-laid-en-turquie-activites-et-recommandations/","name":"Les fêtes de l&#039;Aïd en Turquie : Activités et Recommandations - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-03T15:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-06T12:12:05+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"fr-FR"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Les fêtes de l&#039;Aïd en Turquie : Activités et Recommandations - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-03T15:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-06T12:12:05+03:00","articleSection":"Vie étudiante et Voyages","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Découvrez ce que vous pouvez faire pendant les vacances de l&#039;Aïd en Turquie ! Cliquez ici pour des activités amusantes et des recommandations pour profiter pleinement de ces fêtes traditionnelles.","name":"Les fêtes de l&#039;Aïd en Turquie : Activités et Recommandations - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/les-fetes-de-laid-en-turquie-activites-et-recommandations/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/les-fetes-de-laid-en-turquie-activites-et-recommandations/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/les-fetes-de-laid-en-turquie-activites-et-recommandations/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">En Turquie, les fêtes religieuses (Bayram) ne sont pas seulement des événements spirituels ; ce sont aussi des moments importants où les familles se réunissent, les amitiés se renforcent et les valeurs culturelles sont célébrées.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-bayram-tatilleri-gelenekler-ve-kutlama-sekilleri" class="wp-block-heading">Les fêtes de l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie : Traditions et Célébrations</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">En Turquie, les fêtes religieuses sont célébrées avec diverses traditions. L&#8217;Aïd el-Fitr (Ramazan Bayramı) et l&#8217;Aïd al-Adha (Kurban Bayramı) sont les deux plus importantes, et chacune a ses propres coutumes.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Aïd el-Fitr (Ramazan Bayramı)</strong> : Cette fête marque la fin de la période de jeûne du Ramadan. Le matin de l&#8217;Aïd, les familles se rassemblent dans les mosquées pour une prière collective. Ensuite, elles rendent visite aux aînés, offrant de l&#8217;eau de Cologne et des bonbons. Les enfants reçoivent de l&#8217;argent de poche (bayram harçlığı) et des friandises. Pendant toute la fête, les enfants vont de porte en porte chez les voisins pour récolter des bonbons.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Aïd al-Adha (Kurban Bayramı)</strong> : Cette fête est connue pour la tradition du sacrifice. Les familles sacrifient un animal et partagent la viande avec les plus démunis. C&#8217;est également une période de visites aux amis et à la famille pour échanger les vœux de l&#8217;Aïd.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Pour ces deux fêtes, des plats spéciaux sont préparés à la maison et les invités sont chaleureusement accueillis. Ces traditions renforcent les liens familiaux et favorisent la <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-dayanisma-topluluk-destegi/">solidarité communautaire</a>.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-bayram-tatillerinde-hangi-sehirleri-ziyaret-etmelisiniz" class="wp-block-heading">Quelles villes visiter en Turquie pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd ?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd sont une excellente occasion de découvrir les différentes villes de Turquie. Voici quelques villes à visiter pendant cette période :</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Istanbul</strong> : Riche de son histoire et de sa culture, Istanbul accueille de nombreux événements pendant l&#8217;Aïd. Vous pouvez visiter des monuments emblématiques comme la Mosquée Bleue (Sultanahmet Camii) et Sainte-Sophie (Ayasofya), et faire une croisière sur le Bosphore.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Cappadoce (Kapadokya)</strong> : Célèbre pour ses beautés naturelles et ses cheminées de fées, la Cappadoce offre une expérience immersive dans la nature pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd. Vous pouvez admirer les paysages uniques de la région lors d&#8217;un tour en montgolfière.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Antalya</strong> : Connue pour ses plages ensoleillées et ses ruines historiques, Antalya est idéale pour ceux qui veulent profiter de la mer et du soleil pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd. Vous pouvez vous promener dans le quartier de Kaleiçi et dîner dans d&#8217;excellents restaurants.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Izmir</strong> : Perle de la mer Égée, Izmir séduit par ses beautés historiques et naturelles pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd. Vous pouvez visiter l&#8217;ancienne cité d&#8217;Éphèse (Efes Antik Kenti) et profiter des charmes de Çeşme et Alaçatı.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">5. <strong>Bodrum</strong> : Avec ses plages animées et sa vie nocturne trépidante, Bodrum est une excellente option pour ceux qui cherchent à se détendre et à s&#8217;amuser pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-bayram-gelenekleri-neler-ogrenebilirsiniz" class="wp-block-heading">Traditions de l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie : Ce que vous pouvez apprendre</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les traditions de l&#8217;Aïd reflètent la <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyenin-kulturel-zenginlikleri-gelenekleri/">richesse culturelle</a> de la Turquie. Voici quelques coutumes que vous pourrez découvrir pendant ces fêtes :</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>L&#8217;échange des vœux (Bayramlaşma)</strong> : Se réunir avec la famille et les amis pour échanger les vœux de l&#8217;Aïd contribue à renforcer les liens sociaux. Cette tradition consolide le sentiment d&#8217;unité et de solidarité au sein de la communauté.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>L&#8217;entraide</strong> : Les fêtes de l&#8217;Aïd sont une occasion d&#8217;aider les plus démunis. La distribution de la viande du sacrifice et les dons aux familles dans le besoin sont une partie essentielle de la solidarité sociale.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Les plats spéciaux</strong> : Les repas de fête préparés pour l&#8217;Aïd encouragent le partage au sein des familles. Le baklava, les confiseries et divers plats de viande sont des incontournables des tables de fête.</p>
<h2 id="bayram-tatillerinde-turkiyede-yapilacak-en-iyi-lezzet-duraklari" class="wp-block-heading">Les meilleures spécialités culinaires à déguster en Turquie pendant l&#8217;Aïd</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd ne sont pas seulement faites de célébrations, mais aussi de découvertes gastronomiques. Voici quelques délices à savourer pendant les fêtes :</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Baklava</strong> : Incontournable des fêtes, le baklava est à déguster de préférence à Gaziantep. Cette pâtisserie à base de pistaches et de sirop est la star des tables de l&#8217;Aïd.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Kebab</strong> : Le kebab d&#8217;Adana et le kebab d&#8217;Urfa sont des spécialités à goûter absolument pendant l&#8217;Aïd. Ne manquez pas l&#8217;occasion de les savourer dans les restaurants spécialisés.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Pide</strong> : Les célèbres pides de Kayseri et de Konya sont une option délicieuse pour les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd. Goûtez en particulier celles à la viande hachée (kıymalı) ou aux morceaux de viande (kuşbaşılı).</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Glace (Dondurma)</strong> : Pour vous rafraîchir lors des chaudes journées d&#8217;été, savourez une glace pendant l&#8217;Aïd. La glace de Maraş (Maraş dondurması) est une spécialité particulièrement recommandée.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Simit</strong> : Le simit d&#8217;Istanbul peut devenir un incontournable de vos petits-déjeuners matinaux de l&#8217;Aïd. Déguster un simit frais avec un verre de thé renforce l&#8217;esprit de la fête.</p>
<h2 id="yurt-disindaki-ogrenciler-icin-turkiyede-bayram-tatili-planlama-rehberi" class="wp-block-heading">Guide pour les étudiants étrangers : Planifier ses vacances de l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Pour les étudiants qui étudient à l&#8217;étranger, planifier des vacances pour l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie peut être une expérience très agréable. Voici quelques conseils :</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Vols et hébergement</strong> : Réservez vos billets d&#8217;avion et votre logement à l&#8217;avance pour les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd. Il peut être difficile de trouver de la disponibilité dans les zones touristiques populaires.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Découvrez les traditions</strong> : Vivez les traditions de l&#8217;Aïd en rendant visite à des familles et des amis. Participez aux événements locaux pour mieux comprendre la culture.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Itinéraire de voyage</strong> : Prévoyez de visiter différentes villes de Turquie. Explorez des destinations populaires comme Istanbul, la Cappadoce et Antalya.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Goûtez aux spécialités locales</strong> : Profitez des vacances de l&#8217;Aïd pour découvrir la cuisine locale. Déguster les spécialités de différentes villes vous offrira une expérience inoubliable.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">5. <strong>Participez aux événements sociaux</strong> : Prenez part aux activités sociales organisées pendant l&#8217;Aïd. Les festivals, concerts et autres événements peuvent vous aider à vous faire de nouveaux amis.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie sont riches en découvertes culturelles, en traditions et en moments savoureux. Cette période spéciale est un temps de retrouvailles familiales, de renforcement des amitiés et de célébration des valeurs culturelles. Vous pouvez enrichir cette expérience en visitant différentes villes de Turquie pendant les vacances. N&#8217;oubliez pas que l&#8217;Aïd n&#8217;est pas seulement une fête, mais aussi un moment de rassemblement, de partage et de solidarité. Si vous envisagez de passer les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie, ne manquez pas cette opportunité !</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Foire aux questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quand les fêtes de l&#8217;Aïd sont-elles célébrées en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les fêtes de l&#8217;Aïd sont célébrées deux fois par an : l&#8217;Aïd el-Fitr (Ramazan Bayramı) et l&#8217;Aïd al-Adha (Kurban Bayramı). L&#8217;Aïd el-Fitr marque la fin de la période de jeûne du Ramadan, tandis que l&#8217;Aïd al-Adha est célébré avec la tradition du sacrifice, un devoir religieux.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">À quels types d&#8217;événements puis-je participer pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Pendant les vacances de l&#8217;Aïd, des festivals locaux, des concerts et divers événements sociaux sont organisés. Participer à ces activités peut enrichir votre expérience culturelle.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quels plats sont préparés pour l&#8217;Aïd en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Pour l&#8217;Aïd, on prépare généralement du baklava, des kebabs, des yaprak sarması (feuilles de vigne farcies), des pides et divers desserts. Chaque région a ses propres spécialités culinaires.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-03T12:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-06T09:12:05Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'les-fetes-de-laid-en-turquie-activites-et-recommandations' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"How to Celebrate New Year''s Eve in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Discover the traditions of celebrating New Year''s Eve and other special holidays in Turkey. Read our article now for fun facts and helpful tips for your time abroad!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"How to Celebrate New Year''s Eve in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Discover the traditions of celebrating New Year''s Eve and other special holidays in Turkey. Read our article now for fun facts and helpful tips for your time abroad!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"How to Celebrate New Year''s Eve in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Discover the traditions of celebrating New Year''s Eve and other special holidays in Turkey. Read our article now for fun facts and helpful tips for your time abroad!","canonicalPath":"/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-yilbasi-ve-ozel-gunler/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/bagaimana-tahun-baru-dirayakan-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/","name":"How to Celebrate New Year&#039;s Eve in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-12T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-12T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"How to Celebrate New Year&#039;s Eve in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-12T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-12T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Student Life and Travel","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover the traditions of celebrating New Year&#039;s Eve and other special holidays in Turkey. Read our article now for fun facts and helpful tips for your time abroad!","name":"How to Celebrate New Year&#039;s Eve in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/how-to-celebrate-new-years-eve-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">New Year&#8217;s Eve is a significant milestone in Turkey, both socially and culturally. Every year, on the night connecting December 31st to January 1st, people gather to celebrate the start of a new year. These celebrations are a time for spending with family and friends, as well as for observing various traditions and customs.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-yilbasi-kutlamalarinin-gelenekleri-ve-onemli-noktalari" class="wp-block-heading">Traditions and Highlights of New Year&#8217;s Celebrations in Turkey</h2>
<div id="model-response-message-contentr_fa442e969d94ed21" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" dir="ltr">
<p>New Year&#8217;s celebrations in Turkey largely revolve around gathering with family and close friends, preparing lavish dinner tables, and participating in games of chance.</p>
<h3>1. The Excitement of the National Lottery and Games of Chance</h3>
<p>This is one of Turkey’s oldest and most widespread modern New Year&#8217;s traditions.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>The Milli Piyango New Year&#8217;s Special Draw:</b> The most thrilling moment of New Year&#8217;s Eve is the grand prize drawing of the state lottery. Millions of people try their luck by buying a quarter, half, or full ticket in the final days of the year and follow the draw on television or radio with great excitement.</li>
<li><b>Tombala (Bingo):</b> This is an essential New Year&#8217;s game played within families or among groups of friends. With its simple rules and ability to bring everyone from young to old together, it&#8217;s one of the night&#8217;s most entertaining activities.</li>
</ul>
<h3>2. Preparing Lavish Family Feasts</h3>
<p>New Year&#8217;s Eve means a feast night where people come together to enjoy meticulously prepared meals.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>New Year&#8217;s Turkey:</b> This has become the main course of New Year&#8217;s tables in Turkey. It is usually stuffed with &#8220;iç pilav&#8221; (a seasoned rice pilaf) and roasted to a golden brown, taking center stage on the table. This tradition became popular through interaction with Western culture.</li>
<li><b>Nuts and Fruits:</b> These are indispensable parts of the feast. Traditional nuts like <b>walnuts, hazelnuts, pistachios, and roasted chickpeas</b>, along with fruits like <b>pomegranate, dried figs, and dates</b>, are consumed in abundance.</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. Rituals for Luck and Abundance</h3>
<p>Some popular customs performed with the wish that the new year brings prosperity and luck:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Smashing a Pomegranate:</b> Smashing a pomegranate in front of the house&#8217;s doorstep as the new year begins is a popular tradition for good luck. It is believed that the scattered seeds of the broken pomegranate will bring <b>abundance, prosperity, and luck</b> to the home.</li>
<li><b>Red Underwear:</b> This is common, especially among young people. The belief that wearing red underwear while welcoming the new year will bring <b>love and luck</b> in the coming year is a modernizing tradition.</li>
<li><b>Turning on the Taps:</b> In some places, symbolic rituals like opening the water taps at midnight can be seen, based on the belief in the abundance and prosperity that water brings.</li>
</ul>
<h3>4. Home and Street Decorations</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Decorating a Pine Tree:</b> This is the most distinct visual symbol of New Year&#8217;s, a celebration separate from Christmas in Turkey. Homes, shopping malls, and main streets are adorned with pine trees (New Year&#8217;s trees) decorated with <b>colorful lights, tinsel, and ornaments</b>. This is seen as a symbol of entering the new year with joy and hope.</li>
<li><b>Illuminations:</b> Especially in big cities, central streets like Nişantaşı (Istanbul) and Kızılay (Ankara) are transformed into festival-like areas with dazzling and spectacular light displays.</li>
</ul>
<h3>5. Gift Exchange (New Year&#8217;s Drawing)</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Secret Santa (Drawing Lots):</b> In family, friend, or workplace settings, lots are drawn before New Year&#8217;s. Everyone buys a gift for the person whose name they drew, with a pre-determined budget. The gift exchange takes place on New Year&#8217;s Eve or just before.</li>
<li><b>Tech Gadgets and Clothing:</b> Gift shopping peaks during this period. Tech products and winter clothing are popular gift choices, especially for children and young people.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also check out our post on <a title="Public Holidays in Turkey: What to Do?" href="https://roadtostudy.com//turkiyede-bayram-tatilleri-neler-yapilir/">Public Holidays in Turkey: What to Do?</a></p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-yilbasi-icin-populer-mekanlar-ve-etkinlikler" class="wp-block-heading">Popular Venues and Events for New Year&#8217;s Eve in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On New Year&#8217;s Eve, special events are organized in many parts of Turkey. Celebrations become even more vibrant with various venues and activities, especially in the big cities. Here are some popular places and events for New Year&#8217;s Eve in Turkey:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Istanbul:</strong> New Year&#8217;s parties on the Bosphorus, nightclubs, and special events at hotels are very popular. Taksim Square, in particular, becomes the center of New Year&#8217;s celebrations.</li>
<li><strong>Ankara:</strong> Hotels and restaurants in the city center offer special menus and events for New Year&#8217;s Eve. Additionally, events organized around Anıtkabir also attract attention.</li>
<li><strong>İzmir:</strong> In İzmir, outdoor events and concerts along the Kordon Boyu (waterfront promenade) are essential parts of the new year celebrations.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="yilbasi-alisverisi-turkiyede-nerelerde-ne-alinir" class="wp-block-heading">New Year&#8217;s Shopping: Where and What to Buy in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">New Year&#8217;s shopping is an essential part of the celebrations. Here are some popular places to shop during the New Year&#8217;s period in Turkey:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Shopping Malls:</strong> Major shopping malls in Istanbul like Zorlu Center, Cevahir AVM, and Akmerkez are full of New Year&#8217;s sales and promotions.</li>
<li><strong>Bazaars:</strong> Local markets are a great place to find special gifts and decorations for the New Year. Handmade products and traditional Turkish souvenirs are particularly popular.</li>
<li><strong>Online Shopping:</strong> E-commerce sites make shopping even easier by offering special New Year&#8217;s deals. You can find clothing, accessories, and decorative items here.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="yilbasi-masasi-turk-mutfaginda-geleneksel-lezzetler" class="wp-block-heading">The New Year&#8217;s Table: Traditional Flavors in Turkish Cuisine</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The New Year&#8217;s table is a fantastic opportunity to showcase the rich flavors of Turkish cuisine. Here are some traditional Turkish dishes that might be on the New Year&#8217;s table:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Mezes (Appetizers):</strong> Mezes like artichokes in olive oil, eggplant salad, and hummus are frequently chosen for the New Year&#8217;s table.</li>
<li><strong>Main Courses:</strong> Main dishes such as slow-roasted lamb (kuzu tandır), roasted chicken, or fish are indispensable parts of the New Year&#8217;s feast.</li>
<li><strong>Desserts:</strong> Sweets like baklava, kadayıf, and revani provide the sweet conclusion to New Year&#8217;s celebrations.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Spending New Year&#8217;s Eve in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, New Year&#8217;s is not just the beginning of a new year, but also an opportunity for cultural enrichment and social interaction. This period, when families gather, traditions are kept alive, and special events are held, inspires happiness and hope in many people. If you are thinking of joining these celebrations, you have a great opportunity to discover the richness and traditions Turkey has to offer. Remember, every new year means new beginnings and new hopes!</p>
